b'We Stand Against Racism. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
We believe everyone deserves to feel safe and at home wherever they go. But the killings of George Floyd, Breonna Taylor, Ahmaud Arbery, Rayshard Brooks, and countless others present a more painful reality. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
For years, we have strived to welcome people regardless of what they look like, where they come from, what their abilities are or who they love. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
Marriott International believes Black Lives Matter. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
So, we stand in solidarity for change. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
1) We will build upon our 93-year history of putting people first by elevating the conversation on racism internally with town halls to make sure we continue to listen to our associates and use their perspectives to map our plans and actions. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
2) We will expand our Emerging Leader Program to bring an even sharper focus to the career development needs of our Black associates. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
3) We will continue to provide financial support\xe2\x80\xafto our partners in the Black community, organizations we have been working with for decades \xe2\x80\x93 like the NAACP and National Urban League and others, to help them pursue the mission of equality and social justice, while also engaging with them for advice as we continue to drive progress within Marriott. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
4) We will work to provide an opportunity for our Marriott Bonvoy members to donate points to organizations focused on advancing racial equality and social justice \xe2\x80\x93 donations that we will match to these important organizations. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
5) We call on federal leadership to act with urgency and we will advance Marriott\xe2\x80\x99s policy agenda to advocate for solutions to address barriers to equality and opportunity. \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3 \xe2\x81\xa3\xe2\x81\xa3
We pride ourselves on serving others. And to do that now, we must push for real change. #blacklivesmatter'
b'As we prepare to welcome you back to our hotels around the world, we are committed to providing you with a safe environment.\xe2\x80\x8b'
b'In consultation with experts in public health, we are redefining our cleaning and safety standards in all of our hotels.'

b'We will travel again.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Soon, we will step out from behind our screens.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
We will look each other in the eye\xe2\x80\x94instead of the camera.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
We will clink glasses. We will exchange hugs.\xe2\x81\xa3
We will travel again.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Until then, stay healthy and stay positive.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
We\xe2\x80\x99ll be waiting.\xe2\x81\xa3

b"Earlier this week, Marriott International Group President for Europe, Middle East & Africa Liam Brown joined associates from more than 7,300 properties to celebrate the achievements of women from around the world on International Women's Day. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott"

b"Seema Jain is Marriott International's director of multicultural affairs. Seema has traveled the world with Marriott's Culture Day program -- immersive trainings for hotel staff aimed at fostering multicultural understanding to help ensure welcoming environments. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott"

b'Kori Johnson is general manager of @TheMayflowerHotelDC. She encourages other women to "surround yourself with positive people who are honest with you, but encourage you." #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b'Sherene Hutchinson is a specialty chef at @GrandCaymanMarriott. In 2018, she won Marriott\xe2\x80\x99s Masters of the Craft international cooking competition, beating out more than 2,500 contestants from 270 hotels. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b'Mara de Lima is CEO of Hospitality Property Fund, which owns six Marriott properties, including @WestinCPT in South Africa. Mara began her career working as a management accountant at a hotel and attributes hard work as the backbone of her success. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b'Sharon Gidden is a server at @TorontoAirportMarriott and #MIExcellence honoree. For more than 28 years, Sharon has been smiling, singing, engaging and serving her customers. Often guests return to the hotel just for her stellar service and smile. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b"LaMara Davidson is the executive sous chef for Marriott International's operational support resources team for the Americas. As a woman chef, she takes an active role in mentoring the next generation of young women. #IWD2020\xc2\xa0 #WomenOfMarriott #DiaryOfTheCraft"

b"Sunday is International Women's Day. Marriott International hotels and associates around the world are celebrating the achievements of women by sharing their photos using #IWD2020 and #WomenOfMarriott."

b'Antika Sangamangmool is the assistant chief engineer at @JWMarriottBKK. Together with her team, she is helping to manage the renovation of the luxury hotel, including its 441 guest rooms and four restaurants. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b"Isabella Rubio is the Club Lounge Attendant at @DeltaToronto. After moving to Canada from Venezuela, she was unable to find work for 18 months. But then Isabella heard about @PrincesTrust's Get Into Hospitality program, where she gained valuable skills training that helped her secure a job offer. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott"

b'Brenda Durham is Marriott International\xe2\x80\x99s senior vice president and regional general counsel for the Caribbean and Latin America. Brenda has also worked as a district attorney and served overseas in the military as an Army JAG. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

b"Pamela McClain has been on the job at @RaphaelHotelKC since it opened in 1975, serving as HR manager for the last eight years. A 2019 #MIExcellence honoree, Pamela is also the hotel's historian, ambassador, trainer and cheerleader. @AutographHotels #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott"

b"Joanna Chugh is Marriott International's vice president of finance operations in Europe. Joanna began her Marriott career as a room service manager at a hotel in London and is now responsible for a portfolio of more than 600 hotels. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott"

b'Mary Jiang is the laundry manager at Sanya Marriott Yalong Bay Resort & Spa in Hainan, China, and a #MIExcellence honoree. Mary joined the hotel as a laundry attendant more than 15 years ago and now leads a team of 32 associates. #IWD2020 #WomenOfMarriott'

caption: b"From the time Marriott International began as Hot Shoppes restaurants, women have played an essential role in the business.
